3-11:For example, the robber can observe over time how often the security agent patrols each area .
3-12:With this knowledge, the robber must choose a single house to rob .
3-13:We assume that the robber generally takes a long time to rob a house .
3-14:If the house chosen by the robber is not on the security agent"s route, then the robber successfully robs it .
3-15:Otherwise, if it is on the security agent"s route, then the earlier the house is on the route, the easier it is for the security agent to catch the robber before he finishes robbing it .
