3-35:If the distribution of different robber types is known or inferred from historical data, then the game can be modeled as a Bayesian game [6]. .
4 BAYESIAN GAMES :
4-1:A Bayesian game contains a set of N agents, and each agent n must be one of a given set of types θn .
4-2:For our patrolling domain, we have two agents, the security agent and the robber .
4-3:θ1 is the set of security agent types and θ2 is the set of robber types .
4-4:Since there is only one type of security agent, θ1 contains only one element .
4-5:During the game, the robber knows its type but the security agent does not know the robber"s type .
4-6:For each agent (the security agent or the robber) n, there is a set of strategies σn and a utility function un : θ1 × θ2 × σ1 × σ2 → .
4-7:A Bayesian game can be transformed into a normal form game using the Harsanyi transformation [8] .
4-8:Once this is done, new, linear program based methods for finding high reward strategies for normal form games [5] can be used to find a strategy in the transformed game; this strategy can then be used for the Bayesian game .
4-9:While methods exist for finding Bayes Nash equilibria directly, without the Harsanyi transformation [10], they find only a 312 The Sixth Intl .
