7-24:MIP Nash solves for even fewer robber types within the cutoff time .
7-25:On the other hand, ASAP runs much faster, and is able to solve for at least 20 adversaries for the three house scenarios and for at least 12 adversaries in the four house scenarios within the cutoff time .
7-26:The runtime of ASAP does not increase strictly with the number of robber types for each scenario, but in general, the addition of more types increases the runtime required .
